ğŸ“‚ File and Directory Commands
Command	Description
ls	List files and directories
pwd	Print working directory
cd	Change directory
mkdir	Create a directory
rmdir	Remove an empty directory
rm	Remove files or directories (rm -r for recursive)
cp	Copy files or directories
mv	Move or rename files and directories
touch	Create an empty file
cat	Display file content
more / less	View file content page by page
find	Search for files and directories

ğŸ› ï¸ File Permissions and Ownership
Command	Description
chmod	Change file permissions
chown	Change file owner and group
chgrp	Change group ownership

ğŸ§­ System Information
Command	Description
uname -a	Show system info
df -h	Disk space usage
du -sh <dir>	Disk usage of a directory
top	Real-time system processes
free -h	Memory usage
uptime	System uptime

ğŸ‘¥ User and Process Management
Command	Description
ps	Show running processes
kill	Kill a process by PID
sudo	Run a command as superuser
whoami	Show current user
adduser	Add a user
passwd	Change user password

ğŸŒ Networking
Command	Description
